WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.992
Open Settings, then Operations, then Cancellation Reasons.

p02
00:00:01.219 --> 00:00:04.183
This is a list page,

p03
00:00:04.951 --> 00:00:10.948
and it is the doorway into a shape you will meet on nearly every screen in WashCentral.

p04
00:00:11.511 --> 00:00:14.960
Learn it once here, and the rest of the platform stops surprising you.

p05
00:00:15.394 --> 00:00:16.579
Look across the top.

p06
00:00:16.966 --> 00:00:18.864
Three tiles count the list below:

p07
00:00:19.660 --> 00:00:21.063
how many reasons exist, how many reach the POS, and how many stay hidden.

p08
00:00:21.667 --> 00:00:23.224
Numbers on top, records underneath.

p09
00:00:23.545 --> 00:00:30.587
The same shape you met on the customer lists.

p10
00:00:31.102 --> 00:00:32.444
Now the card itself.

p11
00:00:33.057 --> 00:00:33.700
A title, a search box scoped to these reasons, and one green button to add a record.

p12
00:00:34.006 --> 00:00:42.317
When a list runs long, you search it instead of scrolling.

p13
00:00:42.813 --> 00:00:43.805
Read the columns.

p14
00:00:44.290 --> 00:00:48.566
Each row is a single reason: what it says, and whether the register shows it.

p15
00:00:48.989 --> 00:00:50.580
One row, one record.

p16
00:00:51.098 --> 00:00:54.075
Click any row, and that record opens on a page of its own.

p17
00:00:54.602 --> 00:00:55.583
Drop to the footer.

p18
00:00:56.075 --> 00:00:59.809
Rows per page, a count of what matched, and the page arrows.

p19
00:01:00.135 --> 00:01:05.373
Set it once, read the counter, and you always know how many records you are working through.

p20
00:01:05.373 --> 00:01:06.862
Jump to Refund Reasons.

p21
00:01:07.305 --> 00:01:09.124
Same page, lighter version.

p22
00:01:09.622 --> 00:01:12.612
One tile, one column, the same add button.

p23
00:01:13.049 --> 00:01:18.640
The fields change from list to list, but the shape holds.

p24
00:01:19.071 --> 00:01:19.252
That is the whole point of learning it once.

p25
00:01:19.252 --> 00:01:21.788
Back on Cancellation Reasons, click a row.

p26
00:01:22.143 --> 00:01:23.938
And notice what does not happen.

p27
00:01:24.386 --> 00:01:26.097
No detail page opens.

p28
00:01:26.517 --> 00:01:29.173
This lean reference list keeps you right here;

p29
00:01:29.569 --> 00:01:33.445
its only record action is that green New Record button.

p30
00:01:33.445 --> 00:01:35.399
Now scan the page for record buttons.

p31
00:01:35.850 --> 00:01:36.762
There is no Back, no Edit, no Delete.

p32
00:01:37.048 --> 00:01:38.602
On richer record types you will meet that three-button band; this list simply never grew one.

p33
00:01:39.488 --> 00:01:48.447
Everything it can do sits in New Record.

p34
00:01:48.447 --> 00:01:51.086
Before we open the form, learn its two exits.

p35
00:01:51.922 --> 00:01:53.453
Cancel walks away clean.

p36
00:01:54.198 --> 00:01:59.093
Save Changes writes to the shared tenant, so on the demo you always leave through Cancel.

p37
00:02:00.307 --> 00:02:03.607
A star marks anything the form requires.

p38
00:02:03.607 --> 00:02:06.920
And the delete rule still applies, even without a Delete button here.

p39
00:02:07.509 --> 00:02:11.065
Where other record types carry one, it always asks first.

p40
00:02:11.369 --> 00:02:18.166
Choose No, Keep at that confirmation,

p41
00:02:18.689 --> 00:02:19.001
and treat Yes, Delete as off-limits on anything you did not create.

p42
00:02:19.001 --> 00:02:21.069
Back on the list, open New Record.

p43
00:02:22.019 --> 00:02:25.740
The same form again, blank this time, ready for a fresh entry.

p44
00:02:26.241 --> 00:02:30.686
You are only here to see the layout, so close it the way you closed the edit: Cancel.

p45
00:02:31.030 --> 00:02:32.958
Nothing gets added.

p46
00:02:32.958 --> 00:02:34.935
So that is the pattern on this lean list.

p47
00:02:35.412 --> 00:02:35.921
List, then New Record, then the form, and Cancel back out.

p48
00:02:36.325 --> 00:02:37.305
Two exits keep you safe: Cancel out of a form, No, Keep out of any delete you meet elsewhere.

p49
00:02:37.657 --> 00:02:39.903
One demo quirk to expect: the form header may name a sample record over a blank form.

p50
00:02:40.282 --> 00:02:41.969
That is the tenant, not a bug.

p51
00:02:42.465 --> 00:03:00.640
Richer record types add the detail view, and this rhythm carries straight into them.

